President Obama has announced the appointment of various individuals to the Committee for the Preservation of the White House. The committee's role is to advise on the preservation and interpretation of the museum character of the public rooms in the White House. They will also provide guidance on additions to the permanent collection of fine art and decorative arts objects. The committee works closely with the Executive Residence staff and the White House Historical Association. The goal is to ensure that the White House remains historically accurate and an open, living museum.